.:: Puzzle 4x4-Level-3-2::.
The people have 4 different jobs:  bartender, electrician, photographer, police-officer
4 different pets are kept: horse, mouse, hedgehog, chinchilla
The people's birthday is in 4 different months: january, july, october, september
The people use 4 different means of transport: car, roller, tram, trike
1. the person who's birthday is in october is on the left of the person who's birthday is in july##1
2. the electrician is the owner of the horse##1
3. the person driving the tram is the photographer##1
4. the bartender is between the owner of the mouse and the person driving the car##2
5. the person driving the car is on the left of the person driving the roller##1
6. the person who's birthday is in september is the person driving the trike##1
7. the person who's birthday is in january is on the far right##1
8. the person driving the car is on the far left or far right##3
9. the owner of the mouse is on the left of the owner of the chinchilla##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |      1      |     2     |       3        |      4       |
| Job           | electrician | bartender | police-officer | photographer |
| Pet   | horse  | hedgehog | mouse         | chinchilla      |
| Birthday         | october      | july    | september         | january   |
| Transport     | car         | roller    | trike          | tram         |

